# Accessibility

Baseline: **WCAG 2.2 Level AA**. CI enforces what it can; the rest is on
you. Source of truth: `design-system/accessibility.md`.

## Hard rules

1. **Visible focus ring** on every interactive element. Never
   `outline: none` without a replacement of equal or better contrast.
2. **Accessible name** on every interactive element. Visible label, or
   `aria-label`, or `aria-labelledby`. Icon-only buttons must have one.
3. **44×44 minimum touch target** on touch viewports. The `Button`
   `size="icon"` variant ships at `h-11 w-11`.
4. **Every input has a `<label>`.** Use the `FormField` pattern. Bare
   `<input>` is banned outside L1 primitives.
5. **Reduced motion respected.** Branch on `useReducedMotion()` from
   `@famm/ui`. Tokens already collapse `--duration-*` to 0ms in the
   reduced-motion media query.
6. **Color is never the only signal.** Errors are red *and* labelled. PR
   state is gold *and* labelled. Required fields have an asterisk *and*
   `aria-required`.

## Keyboard

- Every interactive element is reachable by Tab in visual order.
- Escape closes modals and popovers; focus returns to the trigger.
- Arrow keys navigate within composite widgets (tabs, listbox, calendar).
- Enter and Space both activate buttons identically. `<div onClick>`
  doesn't.

## Screen readers

- Live data (timers, set counters, async results) uses
  `aria-live="polite"`. Alerts use `role="alert"`.
- Modals: `aria-modal="true"` and `aria-labelledby` pointing at the
  title.
- Form errors: `aria-invalid="true"` on the control, error message
  associated via `aria-describedby`.
- Decorative icons: `aria-hidden="true"`.

## Contrast

- Body text ≥ 4.5:1; large text ≥ 3:1; meaningful UI graphics ≥ 3:1.
- Tokens are pre-validated. If you introduce a raw color (which you
  shouldn't — see `02-component-rules.mdc`), it's your contrast burden.

## When uncertain

If you're not sure how to make something accessible, **don't ship the
inaccessible version**. Ask. The right answer is often "use the existing
primitive that already handles this".

## What CI enforces

- `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y/recommended` plus stricter overrides
  (`no-autofocus`, `click-events-have-key-events`,
  `no-static-element-interactions`).
- `no-restricted-syntax` bans raw hex/px/rgb and inline `style={}`
  outside L1 primitives.

## What CI doesn't catch (review enforces)

- Logical tab order.
- That an `aria-label` actually describes the action.
- That a live region announces what the user needs.
- That a focus ring is visible against its actual background.
- That a "destructive" button looks destructive in dark mode too.
